docs.abstract: Nikki Haley’s calls for muscular international engagement and cuts to future Social Security benefits have elicited withering attacks from Donald J. Trump. They used to be Republican orthodoxy.
docs.snippet: Nikki Haley’s calls for muscular international engagement and cuts to future Social Security benefits have elicited withering attacks from Donald J. Trump. They used to be Republican orthodoxy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nikki Haley is appealing to voters with policies that recall an era when the Republican Party stood for a fiscal conscience and foreign policy leadership, at a time when the most sacred of federal programs and the international alliances that built the post-World War II era are under enormous strain.

headline.main: Haley’s Policy Pitch Recalls a Bygone Era Before Trump’s Rise
headline.print_headline: Haley’s Policy Pitch Recalls Bygone Era Before Trump’s Rise

docs.abstract: Her chance to beat Donald J. Trump in New Hampshire depends on her ability to win over its famously freethinking voters. Her challenge is that they come in all stripes.
docs.snippet: Her chance to beat Donald J. Trump in New Hampshire depends on her ability to win over its famously freethinking voters. Her challenge is that they come in all stripes.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nikki Haley’s presidential aspirations may hang on a victory in the New Hampshire primary election on Tuesday, powered by her sway with people who do not belong to a political party. It’s not a bad bet in a state where about 40 percent of voters call themselves independents.

headline.main: Nikki Haley Is Chasing Independents. They Have a Mind of Their Own.
headline.print_headline: The Freethinking Bloc That Can Make or Break Haley

byline.original: By Jonathan Weisman, Katie Glueck and Nick Corasaniti

docs.abstract: A self-funding entrepreneur, Mr. Ramaswamy peaked in late August but deflated under attack from his rivals. He dropped out after the Iowa caucuses and endorsed Donald J. Trump.
docs.snippet: A self-funding entrepreneur, Mr. Ramaswamy peaked in late August but deflated under attack from his rivals. He dropped out after the Iowa caucuses and endorsed Donald J. Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: Vivek Ramaswamy, the 38-year-old entrepreneur and political newcomer who briefly made a splash with brash policy proposals and an outsize sense of confidence, dropped out of the race for the Republican White House nomination after a disappointing fourth-place finish in the Iowa caucuses.

headline.main: Vivek Ramaswamy, Wealthy Political Novice Who Aligned With Trump, Quits Campaign

docs.abstract: Republican voters will render a first verdict on the entreaties Donald J. Trump’s rivals have made to move the party past his grip, as he seeks a turbocharged launch to the nomination.
docs.snippet: Republican voters will render a first verdict on the entreaties Donald J. Trump’s rivals have made to move the party past his grip, as he seeks a turbocharged launch to the nomination.
docs.lead_paragraph: The coldest Iowa caucuses in history arrive Monday night amid expectations that Republicans in the state will put former President Donald J. Trump on the march to a third G.O.P. presidential nomination.

headline.main: What to Watch For in the 2024 Iowa Caucuses

docs.abstract: The former Arkansas governor, nowhere in the polls, is running on principle — and on fumes, financially speaking.
docs.snippet: The former Arkansas governor, nowhere in the polls, is running on principle — and on fumes, financially speaking.
docs.lead_paragraph: Asa Hutchinson sat under the fluorescent lights of a windowless conference room just off the main convention hall at the Prairie Meadows Casino and Hotel in Altoona, Iowa, on Thursday, explaining why there was a mission to the madness of his 2024 campaign for the presidency.

headline.main: Asa Hutchinson, Tilting at a Trump-Branded Windmill, Hangs On
headline.print_headline: Hutchinson Hangs On, With Principles and Little Else

docs.abstract: The former president’s legal jeopardy offers an obvious line of attack for Nikki Haley and Ron DeSantis, but fears of voter blowback mean that cudgel remains largely unused.
docs.snippet: The former president’s legal jeopardy offers an obvious line of attack for Nikki Haley and Ron DeSantis, but fears of voter blowback mean that cudgel remains largely unused.
docs.lead_paragraph: It is an obvious line of attack that has been creeping into the arsenal of rivals trying to stop former President Donald J. Trump ahead of the Iowa caucuses on Monday — if nominated to be the Republican Party’s White House standard-bearer, the former president could very well be a convicted criminal by Election Day.

headline.main: A Convicted Criminal as the Nominee? Trump’s Rivals Avoid Even Raising It
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Rivals Strain to Avoid Discussing the Possibility He Might Be Convicted

docs.abstract: How the former president is trying to wrap up the Republican nomination before any court case can stop him.
docs.snippet: How the former president is trying to wrap up the Republican nomination before any court case can stop him.
docs.lead_paragraph: As former President Donald J. Trump enters an election year leading his Republican rivals by wide margins in the polls, multiple court cases are taking up an increasing amount of his campaign schedule. They have been integrated into his messaging and fund-raising efforts, and his campaign staff has been developing a strategy to lock up his nomination, regardless of what happens in court.

byline.original: By Michael Barbaro, Summer Thomad, Luke Vander Ploeg, Rachelle Bonja, Rikki Novetsky, Olivia Natt, Rachel Quester, Brendan Klinkenberg, Lexie Diao, Pat McCusker, Dan Powell, Marion Lozano and Alyssa Moxley

docs.abstract: The blockbuster ruling by Colorado’s Supreme Court would seem to give Donald Trump’s challengers an avenue of attack, but far behind in the polls, they are skirting the issue.
docs.snippet: The blockbuster ruling by Colorado’s Supreme Court would seem to give Donald Trump’s challengers an avenue of attack, but far behind in the polls, they are skirting the issue.
docs.lead_paragraph: A state high court’s decision that the Republican front-runner for the White House is disqualified from office might seem like a pretty good opening for his ostensible G.O.P. challengers.

headline.main: With Trump Declared an ‘Insurrectionist,’ His Rivals Pull Their Punches, Again
headline.print_headline: New Blow to Front-Runner, But Rivals Resist Pouncing

docs.abstract: Opinion is split between those wanting the war to end and those pressing for a definitive Israeli victory, and the divide is starkest among older and younger generations.
docs.snippet: Opinion is split between those wanting the war to end and those pressing for a definitive Israeli victory, and the divide is starkest among older and younger generations.
docs.lead_paragraph: Voters broadly disapprove of the way President Biden is handling the bloody strife between Israelis and Palestinians, a New York Times/Siena College poll has found, with younger Americans far more critical than older voters of both Israel’s conduct and the administration’s response to the war in Gaza.

headline.main: Poll Finds Wide Disapproval of Biden on Gaza, and Little Room to Shift Gears
headline.print_headline: Most Disapprove Of Biden On Gaza, Survey Indicates
